sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS private_data_count
FROM data_records
WHERE is_private = 1;

SELECT COUNT(data_id) AS linked_data_count
FROM user_data_links
WHERE user_id = 1 AND is_active = 1;

SELECT title
FROM data_records
WHERE is_private = 1;

external_knowledge:
1 megabyte = 1048576 bytes; 
"past month" refers to the time period from the current date minus one month up to the current date; 
"active users" are users with 'is_active' = 1; 
"non-private data records" are records with 'is_private' = 0.
